					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just reduced the bar by AT LEAST 75% just by adding a Big ass Capacitor right across the regulator output.<br /><br />Im sorry if this has been established before, and it probably was, I apologize I did not read the whole thread but I just noticed that. And thought this was one heck of a dirty easy fix. <br /><br />So whatever causes the bar transmits it at least in good part through the 5v rail. <br /><br />I used a 4700 uf @10v ( huge can ), basically the largest capacitance cap I had on hand, and just soldered it there on the regulator.</div>

